## Round 3 — 2026-06-12 — convergence check on v3

## 1. Round-2 Collisions

1. **Degraded synthesis — RESOLVED.** P7 permits provisional claims with explicit machine-generated caveats when trusted evidence is insufficient.

2. **Promotion rule — RESOLVED.** P7 defines automatic promotion by profile trust bar plus no open contradiction, explicitly excluding corroboration.

3. **Data model + read-only view — PARTIAL.** Reports, claim base, and dossier view are clearly separated, but report immutability conflicts with universal conflict surfacing.

## 2. New Contradictions

1. P2 says run reports are immutable and “never rewritten,” while P5 requires conflicts to be surfaced “wherever the subject is rendered (run reports, dossier view).” A conflict discovered later cannot appear in an existing immutable report.

2. The rendering contract says “all rendering (run reports, dossier view)” uses one canonical path, but run reports are stored source-grounded prose while dossier views are generated from mutable claim state. These cannot share one rendering path without either regenerating reports or weakening what “one canonical render path” means.

3. Scope still calls the mechanism “confidence-gated ingestion,” while P1 explicitly says “ingestion is unconditional” and only promotion is gated.

## 3. Convergence Call

**ANOTHER ROUND**

Blocking issue: Define whether immutable run reports are historical artifacts or live rendered surfaces; the document currently requires them to be both.

